                row of three dots below T2. T4 adds a row of four dots below T3. 
                T5 adds a row of five dots below T4.
              </description>
            </image>
          </figure>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  List the number of dots in each of <m>T_1, T_2, T_3, T_4, T_5</m>.
                  Do not add these five numbers.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Sketch <m>T_6</m>. How many dots does it have?
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Without drawing the picture, how many dots should <m>T_{10}</m>
                  have? Why?
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  In <xref ref="right-isos-tri-5"/>, the dots in <m>T_5</m> have been  
                  rearranged to form an isosceles right triangle, labeled <m>S_5</m>. Then a second copy 
                  of this configuration has been made and rotated so that together they 
                  form a rectangle, labeled <m>R_5</m>. 
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      Use this process to sketch <m>R_2</m>, <m>R_3</m>, and <m>R_4</m>. What should 
                      <m>R_1</m> look like?
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      What is the number of dots (blue and red together) in each row of <m>R_5</m>?
                    </li>
                    <li>
